  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhanced flood and drought resilience</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Climate Proof and Eco-Smart Disaster Risk Reduction Project was implemented in 30 communities, in the districts of Katakwi and Kapelebyong.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project targeted 1,400 households (approximately 8,400 people) with approximately 10,000 secondary beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To reduce vulnerability and enhance resilience of households in Amuria and Katakwi districts in Teso Sub-region, North Eastern Uganda

Specific objectives: 

To reduce vulnerability and build household resilience against the impacts of disasters among communities of Amuria and Katakwi districts by 2018. 

To build capacity of community institutions/structures to strengthen and promote disaster risk reduction.</narrative>
  </description>
